  "explanation": "The defendant committed a serious breach of professional trust by embezzling $25,000 from their employer in their capacity as an accountant. In determining the appropriate sentence, the court has factored in several mitigating elements: the defendant has no prior criminal history and has demonstrated remorse by actively working to partially pay back the stolen funds. While these factors justify leniency and a deviation from the maximum possible sentence, a period of incarceration is still warranted to serve as a deterrent and to respect the gravity of the theft. Accordingly, a sentence of 6 months of incarceration is imposed, along with a mandate for full restitution of the remaining balance.",
  "verdict": 6
}
